                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#1v">Fol. 1v</locus>
                        <desc>St. George slaying the dragon.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Unidentified salām-hymn for St Mary (?).  </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ርግብ፡ ሰላማዊት፡ ወንጽር፡ መንፈስዊት፡ ሰ፡ ለ፡ በሥምረተ፡
                              አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሰ፡ ለ፡ እምትካት፡ የኀረየኪ፡ ሰ፡ ለ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ፡ ጽልዮተኪ፡ በጽሐ፡
                              ከመ፡ ኢይሙት፡ ገብርኪ፡…</q>
                           
                           <note> Written by the same hand as that of Additio 2 (same as that of the
                              main text?), in one column. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#204v">f. 204v</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Unidentified text.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                               ኦእግዚእየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልድ፡ ዋህድ፡ ቃለ፡
                              እግዚአብሔር። አብ፡ ዘበተከ፡ እምኔነ፡ ኵሎ፡ ማዕሠ(ረ)፡ ኃጣውኢነ፡ በሕማማቲከ፡ መኅየዊት፡ ወመድኀኒት፡
                              ዘነፋሕከ፡ ላዕለ፡ ገጸ፡ አርዳኢከ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ወላዕከኒከ፡ ንጹሐን፡ ወትቤሎሙ፡ ንሥኡ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሰእለ፡
                              ኃደግሙ፡ ለሰብእ፡ ኀጢአተ።… </q>
                           
                           <note> Note on how Jesus broke the bounds of sins by means of His
                              Passion, and how He blew upon the apostles and ministers faces the
                              Holy Spirit, in order to redeem mankind from sins. The same hand as
                              that of Additio 1 (the same as that of the main text?). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- Excerpts of hymns for the Good Friday (?) added in the
                           upper margins of <locus target="#122v">122v</locus>, 123r, 123v, 127v,
                           128r.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>  - Crude notes written in blue, red pen and pencil on fols 4r,
                              33v, 34v, 51r, 52r, 53v, 55v, 103, 148v, 154v, 171v, 173v.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc> - The
                           words ʾǝläf kämäč̣ärräšaw are written, framed by dots, in the margin
                           between columns on <locus target="#13r">13r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>  - Numbers (?)
                           are added between columns on fols 37v, 44r, 49v and in the left margin of
                              <locus target="#76r">76r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc> - Tamallas-signs (in the shape
                           of +) indicating the place where the omissions, written in the margin, or
                           interlineally, belong: <locus target="#28r">28r</locus>, 33r. </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc> -
                           Immediate corrections marked by thin lines below words (e.g. <locus target="#32ra">32ra</locus>, 54va, 63vb, 84va, 113vb) and by thin
                              lines above (<locus target="#128vb">128vb</locus>).</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                           <desc> - Omissions or
                              corrections are written interlineally, e.g., <locus target="#13va">13va</locus>, 13vb, 20ra, 48ra, 68vb, 80ra, 106rb, 132vb.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e8">
                           <desc>  -
                           Unfilled spaces left for rubrication on <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>
                              (Additio 1), 203va, 204rb, 204v (Additio 2).</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e9">
                           <desc>  - Lacuna in <locus target="#72rb">72rb</locus>: the text interrupts on <locus target="#72ra">72ra</locus> and resumes on <locus target="#72va">72va</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e10">
                           <desc> - The scribe reduced the size of the script on
                              <locus from="161vb" to="162rb">161vb-162rb</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e11">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- A strip of textile (for navigating in the text?)
                              is inserted on <locus target="#82r">fol. 82r</locus>. - Thread for
                              navigating in the text on fols. 12r, 33 (?). - A thread (for
                              navigating in the text?) is inserted within the parchment´s hole in
                              the bottom corner of <locus target="#74">fol.
                           74</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
